in love with African-American song.

00:33:20.230 --> 00:33:24.760
There are I think many
reasons for it.

00:33:24.760 --> 00:33:28.150
Reason one, he was hearing
some extraordinary music

00:33:28.150 --> 00:33:29.750
that he never heard before.

00:33:29.750 --> 00:33:34.200
Another thing was Dvorak was deeply
religious and as you may know,

00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:38.940
Czech folksongs generally are about
drinking wine and chasing girls.

00:33:38.940 --> 00:33:42.330
And suddenly he found what he
thought was an American folk music,

00:33:42.330 --> 00:33:43.630
which was biblical.

00:33:43.630 --> 00:33:47.280
It was all about Daniel in the
lion's den and go down Moses.

00:33:47.280 --> 00:33:51.850
He very quickly hooked up with
Harry T. Burley, who was studying

00:33:51.850 --> 00:33:55.320 position:56%
