00:34:11.150 --> 00:34:15.790
like an authentic source
for what this music was.

00:34:15.790 --> 00:34:21.530
Dvorak also was in with a group
of people who felt that because

00:34:21.530 --> 00:34:26.220
of the history of slavery
it wasn't only

00:34:26.220 --> 00:34:30.800
that African-American music was
expressive or very expressive

00:34:30.800 --> 00:34:33.020
that it was the most expressive.

00:34:33.020 --> 00:34:36.580
That it was the music that
should be the foundation

00:34:36.580 --> 00:34:38.120
for an American style.

00:34:38.120 --> 00:34:40.230
And Dvorak in a long interview

00:34:40.230 --> 00:34:43.840
with a yellow journalist named
James Creelman, whose signature,

00:34:43.840 --> 00:34:47.500
